{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast with POLD3-directed sgRNAs, the sgRNAs targeting other Polζ subunit genes dropped out even in the absence of TMZ-treatment (Fig. 5i).",
    "However, sgRNAs against other BIR factors showed a dropout pattern similar to POLD3-directed sgRNAs (Fig. 5i).",
    "We infer that the role of POLD3 in BIR is important for RAD18-deficient GBM to tolerate TMZ.",
    "Results of competitive growth assays in Supplementary Fig. 6A, B also demonstrate the effects of deficiencies in FANCD2, PRKDC and POLD3 on TMZ tolerance in U373 cells.",
    "Additionally, we validate the interactions of RAD18 with POLD3 and CHK2 using U87 GBM cells (Supplementary Fig. 6C, D)."
  ]
}